HEADWORD: Crotonine
<hw>Cro"ton*ine</hw> <pr>(kr?"t?n-?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A supposed alkaloid obtained from croton oil by
boiling it with water and magnesia, since found to be merely a magnesia
soap of the oil.</def> <rj><au>Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crotonylene</ent>⟦br⟧
